      "message": "[Major] Line 39: Removing the in-flight connection guard changes behavior: repeated SyncChannelHandler::connect calls for the same device can now enqueue multiple simultaneous sync-channel connection attempts because uniqueName makes each request distinguishable instead of coalescing them. That can create duplicate sync channels, duplicated synchronization work, and extra socket/channel state. Keep the duplicate-attempt guard around the logical channel name while still passing uniqueName to connectDevice.\\n```suggestion\\n    if (connectionManager_.isConnecting(deviceId, channelName)) {\\n        JAMI_LOG(\\\"Already connecting to {}\\\", deviceId);\\n        return;\\n    }\\n    connectionManager_.connectDevice(deviceId,\\n                                     channelName,\\n                                     std::move(cb),\\n                                     dhtnet::ConnectDeviceOptions {.forceNewSocket \u003d false, .uniqueName \u003d true});\\n```",
